Welcome to my development environment home!

The plan here is to... 
Use a Debian OS (WSL) on a Windows machine.
Use Nix package manager to manage most software.
Use Git to version control work and synchronize it between Windows and WSL.

Debian OS setup instructions
1. Download and Run Debian from Microsoft Store on Windows OS, WSL will just run it.
2. Using apt install curl, xz-utils, git, and wget
3. install nix via curl (find cmd for latest version here https://nixos.org/download/)

First time VSCode setup
1. Open it from Windows
2. Set Debian to be default terminal
3. Run ```code -r .``` in a WSL directory, you will be prompted to install VSCode Server via wget

Maintaining dependencies
1. Use scripts to dump all version information from each app into nice text files
2. apt.txt, curl.txt, winget.txt, nix.txt, etc...
3. anything contained to a nix shell, output the versions to a file called nix.txt local to that directory

Git
1. On WSL make the home (username) directory a repo. Host this on github so I can get it anywhere.
2. Make individual projects repos, and host their remotes on Windows. 
3. Make local windows copies of the branches, not just remotes, so I can see source.
4. On Windows, use Obsidian in the home directory, so that I can build notes about my apps.

  Windows
    User/me/Desktop/home
      remotes/
      projects/
      obsidian-vault

